Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @red pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into 2cm wide strips. Pop onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of the
oven until soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, tear the @ciabatta{1} into small
chunks for the croutons. Pop on another baking tray with the
@premium tomato mix{1}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} (thinly sliced). Trim
the @green beans{1} then chop in half. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped)
(stalks and all). Zest, then cut the @lemon{1}(zested and cut into wedges) into
wedges. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}, chop in half widthways then
separate the leaves.

Coarsely crush the @black peppercorns{1/2} in a #pestle and mortar{} along with
a good pinch of @salt{}. TIP: If you don't have a pestle and mortar, put the
@black peppercorns{} in a #sandwich bag{} and crush using the base of a
#saucepan{}. Tip the crushed pepper onto a #plate{} then pop the @swordfish steak{2}
in the pepper until evenly coated on both sides. Press the pepper into the fish
to ensure it sticks. IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw fish.

In a #large bowl{}, mix the @red wine vinegar{1}, @Dijon mustard{1/2} and
@olive oil{2} together, keep to one side. Heat a splash of oil in a
#large frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the green beans and
onion. Stir-fry until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic when
the beans are cooked and cook for a further ~{30%seconds}. Transfer the beans
and onion to the #bowl{} with the dressing and turn to coat the beans. Allow
to cool.

Wipe out the #frying pan{} with some #kitchen paper{} and return to a medium-high
heat with a splash of oil. When hot, add the swordfish steaks and cook until
browned, ~{4-5%minutes} on each side. IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque
in the centre. Finish with a squeeze of lemon juice. Whilst the fish cooks,
crumble the @feta cheese{1}.

Add the leaves to the bowl with the beans in and toss to coat. Share between
your #plates{}. Sprinkle the croutons around then top with the roasted pepper,
tomatoes, @black olives{30}, feta and @walnuts{1}. Top the salad with the
swordfish and a sprinkle of lemon zest and parsley. Enjoy!